# Cursor Prompt вЂ” RealLives Website React Conversion

---

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

You are converting the RealLives website from plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript into a modern React application. This is a large, multi-section website with a unique nested structure. Read this entire prompt before writing a single line of code. Every decision below is intentional.

---

## SITE ARCHITECTURE (Understand This First)

The site has a layered structure:

```
/ (root)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Portal Page вЂ” two cards: "RealLives" and "ChangemakerIndex" (just a link out)

/reallives
в””в”Ђв”Ђ RealLives Landing вЂ” image carousel + 4 entry cards + 2 CTAs + unique footer
    в”‚
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ [CTA 1] /reallives/licenses
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ License Hub вЂ” 4 cards (school, university, homeschooler, gamer)
    в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/licenses/school        в†’ School license detail page
    в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/licenses/university     в†’ University license detail page
    в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/licenses/homeschooler   в†’ Homeschooler license detail page
    в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/licenses/gamer          в†’ Gamer license detail page
    в”‚           Each license detail page has 2 CTAs:
    в”‚             вЂў "Visit Website"  в†’ /reallives/<type> (the sub-site)
    в”‚             вЂў "Buy License"    в†’ /reallives/register/<type> (registration form)
    в”‚
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ [CTA 2] /reallives/login
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ Login Page
    в”‚
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/register/school          в†’ School registration form
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/register/university      в†’ University registration form
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/register/homeschooler    в†’ Homeschooler registration form
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ /reallives/register/gamer           в†’ Gamer registration form

/reallives/school         в†’ School sub-site (own navbar + dynamic footer)
/reallives/university     в†’ University sub-site
/reallives/homeschooler   в†’ Homeschooler sub-site
/reallives/gamer          в†’ Gamer sub-site (unique, different design)
```

Each sub-site (school, university, homeschooler, gamer) is a self-contained website with its own navbar and pages. School, university, and homeschooler share approximately 90% of their components and layout вЂ” only their content differs. The gamer sub-site is visually distinct but still reuses common pages like About Us, Contact Us, etc.

### Two distinct footer types

There are two completely different footer components in this project:

1. **`LandingFooter`** вЂ” used only on `/reallives` (the landing page). Has its own unique About and Contact Us content that is separate from any sub-site. Lives in `components/landing/LandingFooter/`.

2. **`Footer`** (dynamic sub-site footer) вЂ” used inside every sub-site (school, university, homeschooler, gamer). Dynamically renders all navbar links for the current sub-site by reading from the site's nav config in its content file. This means if a new page is added to the school navbar, the school footer automatically includes it вЂ” there is no separate footer link list to maintain.

Do not mix these up. They are different components with different purposes.

---

## TECH STACK

- **React** (with hooks)
- **Vite** as the build tool
- **React Router v6** for routing
- **CSS Modules** for component-scoped styles
- **CSS custom properties (variables)** for theming (light/dark mode)
- No CSS frameworks (no Tailwind, no Bootstrap) unless already present in the original project

